{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883627641,"sessionID":"ses_28516c8a4ffeyklEf33zHwrJZe","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae9a26c001T6QHcx1n03chui","messageID":"msg_d7ae98495001kBplJQHh1YBsc3","sessionID":"ses_28516c8a4ffeyklEf33zHwrJZe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f8bfd8ac7ba34babb8f35f94","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # CI/CD Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Pull request build verification\n9: The system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n12: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n13: - **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n14: - **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\n17: The system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n20: - **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n21: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n22: - **THEN** it SHALL use Go `1.24` and execute `make lint`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Code generation check\n25: The system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Regenerate and diff\n28: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, or `Makefile`\n29: - **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs with Go `1.24.4`\n30: - **THEN** it SHALL run `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`)\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Go test coverage reporting\n33: The system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, optionally uploading to Codecov.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Coverage command\n36: - **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches (broad glob excluding some media/docs per workflow)\n37: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage job runs with Go `1.24`\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` and upload `coverage.out` as an artifact\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: E2E testing on Kind\n41: The system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: E2E job lifecycle\n44: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n45: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`, install Kind tool `v0.30.0` (`install_only: true`), run `make e2e` with Go `1.23`, upload `e2e-logs` on failure, and always run `make e2e-clean`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Python SDK unit tests\n49: The system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Editable install and pytest\n52: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `sdk-python/**`\n53: - **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests job runs with Python `3.12` in `sdk-python/`\n54: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install pytest`, `pip install -e .`, and run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: Python lint\n57: The system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Ruff check\n60: - **GIVEN** path filter matches `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, or the workflow file\n61: - **WHEN** the Python Lint job runs with Python `3.10`\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL `pip install ruff` and run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: Spelling check (codespell)\n65: The system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Codespell invocation\n68: - **GIVEN** checkout complete\n69: - **WHEN** codespell runs after backup/remove of `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` at repo root (and nested copies per `find`)\n70: - **THEN** it SHALL use `pip install codespell` and run codespell with `--check-filenames`, specified `--skip` globs, and `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn` on `.`, then restore backed-up files\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Copyright header check\n73: The system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Copyright workflow\n76: - **GIVEN** path filter marks `copyright` (all paths minus exclusions for md/svg/png/docs/.github per workflow)\n77: - **WHEN** the job runs\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL install `moreutils` (`sponge`), run `make gen-copyright`, and `git diff --exit-code`\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Release image publication\n81: The system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Tag selects image tag\n84: - **GIVEN** a `push` event\n85: - **WHEN** `github.ref_type` is `tag`, environment `TAG` SHALL be `github.ref_name`; otherwise `TAG` SHALL be `latest`\n86: - **THEN** the job SHALL log in to `ghcr.io` with `GITHUB_TOKEN` and run `make docker-buildx-push*`, setting `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` and per-image `*_IMAGE=<name>:${TAG}`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Workflow approval for first-time contributors\n89: The system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Approve action_required runs\n92: - **GIVEN** `pull_request_target` on `main` or `release-**` with label/sync events\n93: - **WHEN** the contributor is not first-time (more than one PR) or PR has `ok-to-test`\n94: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required` and call `approveWorkflowRun` for each\n\n(End of file - total 94 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# CI/CD Specification\n\n## Purpose\nAutomate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pull request build verification\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker build in CI\n- **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*`\n- **WHEN** the “Agentcube CI Workflow” job runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL checkout the repository, set up Docker Buildx, verify `docker`/`buildx` versions, and run `make docker-build`\n\n### Requirement: Go lint on changed Go code\nThe system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n\n#### Scenario: Path-filtered lint\n- **GIVEN** a pull request and path filter matches `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, or `.github/workflows/lint.yml`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/spec.md","time":{"start":1775883627617,"end":1775883627640}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883627644,"sessionID":"ses_28516c8a4ffeyklEf33zHwrJZe","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae9a7d7001chcOVxyRgxJQ3i","messageID":"msg_d7ae98495001kBplJQHh1YBsc3","sessionID":"ses_28516c8a4ffeyklEf33zHwrJZe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d794da4d829f4ffc84a2dc2b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n4: \n5: ## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n6: \n7: | Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n8: |----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n9: | `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n10: | `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n11: | `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n12: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n13: | `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n14: | `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n15: | `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n16: | `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n17: | `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n18: | `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n19: | `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n20: | `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |\n21: \n22: ### Workflow notes\n23: \n24: - **`e2e.yml`**: Uses Kind action with `install_only: true` so the cluster is created by `run_e2e.sh` (`kind create cluster`), avoiding double-creation.\n25: - **`test-coverage.yml`**: `workflow_call` declares `CODECOV_TOKEN` optional for reusable invocation; PR runs use the repo secret when configured.\n26: - **`build-push-release.yml`**: Uses older action major versions (`checkout@v3`, `setup-go@v4`, `buildx@v2`) than most other workflows.\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## E2E test setup (`test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n31: \n32: ### Kind cluster\n33: \n34: | Item | Value / behavior |\n35: |------|------------------|\n36: | Default cluster name | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` → `agentcube-e2e` |\n37: | Creation | `kind create cluster --name \"${E2E_CLUSTER_NAME}\"` if missing; if exists and `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER=true` (default), delete then recreate |\n38: | CI alignment | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` installs Kind **v0.30.0** via `helm/kind-action@v1` (`install_only: true`) |\n39: | Skip setup | `E2E_SKIP_SETUP=true` skips `run_setup` and assumes an existing cluster |\n40: \n41: ### CRD / agent-sandbox installation\n42: \n43: Applied via `kubectl apply --validate=false` after downloading release assets (URLs built from `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`, default **`v0.1.1`**):\n44: \n45: 1. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/manifest.yaml`\n46: 2. `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox/releases/download/${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}/extensions.yaml`\n47: \n48: ### Images pre-pulled and loaded into Kind\n49: \n50: - `registry.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/agent-sandbox-controller:${AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION}`\n51: - `python:3.9-slim` (echo agent workload)\n52: \n53: Local images built and loaded:\n54: \n55: - `make docker-build` → default `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` **`workloadmanager:latest`**\n56: - `make docker-build-router` → **`agentcube-router:latest`**\n57: - `make docker-build-picod` → **`picod:latest`**\n58: - `REDIS_IMAGE` default **`redis:7-alpine`** (Deployment + Service in namespace)\n59: \n60: ### Helm (AgentCube chart)\n61: \n62: | Item | Value |\n63: |------|--------|\n64: | Chart path | `manifests/charts/base` |\n65: | Release / namespace | `agentcube` in `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (default `agentcube`), `--create-namespace` |\n66: | Redis addr | `redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379`, password empty |\n67: | Workload manager image | `repository=workloadmanager`, `tag=latest` |\n68: | Router image | `repository=agentcube-router`, `tag=latest` |\n69: | Router RBAC | `router.rbac.create=true`, `router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router` |\n70: | Extra env (JSON via `--set-json`) | Workload manager: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`, `JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE=agentcube`; Router: `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n71: | Wait | `helm upgrade --install ... --wait` |\n72: \n73: ### Kubernetes fixtures applied during setup\n74: \n75: | Path | Purpose |\n76: |------|---------|\n77: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | `AgentRuntime` `echo-agent` in `agentcube` |\n78: | Generated from `echo_agent.yaml` (sed) | `echo-agent-short-ttl` with `sessionTimeout: \"30s\"` for TTL tests |\n79: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` `e2e-code-interpreter` in `agentcube` |\n80: \n81: Warm-pool Go tests apply `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` at runtime (not in initial `kubectl apply` list in the shell script).\n82: \n83: ### Port forwards and health checks\n84: \n85: - Workload manager: `kubectl port-forward svc/workloadmanager` → `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8080**) → pod 8080\n86: - Router: `kubectl port-forward svc/agentcube-router` → `ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT` (default **8081**) → pod 8080\n87: - Readiness: `curl` to `http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}/health` and `http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}/health/live`\n88: \n89: ### Auth for tests\n90: \n91: - ServiceAccount `e2e-test` in `agentcube` + `ClusterRoleBinding` to `workloadmanager` clusterrole\n92: - API token: `kubectl create token e2e-test -n agentcube --duration=24h` → `API_TOKEN`\n93: \n94: ### Python venv for E2E\n95: \n96: - Directory: `E2E_VENV_DIR` (default `/tmp/agentcube-e2e-venv`)\n97: - `python3 -m venv`, `pip install -e ./sdk-python`, verify `import agentcube`\n98: \n99: ### Test commands invoked by `run_e2e.sh`\n100: \n101: **Go** (from repository root):\n102: \n103: ```bash\n104: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"http://localhost:${WORKLOAD_MANAGER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n105: ROUTER_URL=\"http://localhost:${ROUTER_LOCAL_PORT}\" \\\n106: API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n107: go test -v ./test/e2e/...\n108: ```\n109: \n110: **Python** (after `cd` to `test/e2e`):\n111: \n112: ```bash\n113: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=\"...\" ROUTER_URL=\"...\" API_TOKEN=$API_TOKEN \\\n114: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE=\"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n115: \"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py\n116: ```\n117: \n118: (`test_codeinterpreter.py` uses `unittest.main()` and appends `--verbose` if missing.)\n119: \n120: ### Failure artifacts\n121: \n122: On test failure, `collect_component_logs` writes under `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (CI: `${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`): workload manager, router, and sandbox pod logs/describes.\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## Test directory structure\n127: \n128: ```\n129: test/\n130: ├── OWNERS\n131: └── e2e/\n132:     ├── README.md\n133:     ├── __init__.py\n134:     ├── run_e2e.sh\n135:     ├── e2e_test.go\n136:     ├── test_codeinterpreter.py\n137:     ├── echo_agent.yaml\n138:     ├── e2e_code_interpreter.yaml\n139:     └── e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### Fixture paths (relative to repo root unless noted)\n143: \n144: | Fixture | Description |\n145: |---------|-------------|\n146: | `test/e2e/echo_agent.yaml` | Echo `AgentRuntime` for router invocation tests |\n147: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter.yaml` | Standard `CodeInterpreter` (`e2e-code-interpreter`, namespace `agentcube`) |\n148: | `test/e2e/e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml` | `CodeInterpreter` with `warmPoolSize: 2` in `default` (loaded by Go tests from **package cwd** as `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`) |\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Go test commands and flags in CI\n153: \n154: | Workflow / entrypoint | Command | Flags / notes |\n155: |------------------------|---------|----------------|\n156: | `test-coverage.yml` | `go test` | `-race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...` |\n157: | `e2e.yml` via `make e2e` → `run_e2e.sh` | `go test` | `-v ./test/e2e/...` with env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `API_TOKEN` |\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## Python test commands in CI\n162: \n163: | Workflow | Working dir | Command |\n164: |----------|-------------|---------|\n165: | `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `sdk-python` | `python -m pip install --upgrade pip`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` |\n166: | `e2e.yml` (via `run_e2e.sh`) | Invoked from `test/e2e/` | `\"$E2E_VENV_DIR/bin/python\" test_codeinterpreter.py` (unittest, verbosity 2) |\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## Key Make targets referenced by CI\n171: \n172: | Target | Referenced in | Role |\n173: |--------|----------------|------|\n174: | `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `run_e2e.sh` | Build workload manager image |\n175: | `docker-build-router` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build router image |\n176: | `docker-build-picod` | `run_e2e.sh` | Build picod image |\n177: | `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image (`IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`) |\n178: | `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n179: | `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n180: | `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n181: | `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n182: | `lint` | `lint.yml` | `golangci-lint` (project default) |\n183: | `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code up to date |\n184: | `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers for check |\n185: \n186: ---\n187: \n188: ## Additional reference: E2E README vs script\n189: \n190: `test/e2e/README.md` states Go **1.24+** and generic “install CRDs and agent-sandbox”; the **CI workflow** pins Go **1.23** for E2E, and **run_e2e.sh** pins **agent-sandbox `v0.1.1`** by default (overridable via `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`).\n\n(End of file - total 190 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CI/CD — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/.github/workflows/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/test/`, and (for Make targets) `/tmp/agentcube-ref/Makefile`.\n\n## GitHub Actions workflows (summary table)\n\n| Filename | Workflow `name` | Trigger events | Path filters (dorny/paths-filter or notes) | Jobs | Key steps | Env vars (job/step) | Secrets |\n|----------|-----------------|----------------|---------------------------------------------|------|-----------|---------------------|---------|\n| `main.yml` | Agentcube CI Workflow | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `build` | Checkout; Docker Buildx setup; verify Docker; `make docker-build` | — | — |\n| `e2e.yml` | Agentcube E2E Tests | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none)* | `e2e-test` | Checkout; Go 1.23; `helm/kind-action@v1` **install_only** Kind v0.30.0, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`; `export ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`; `make e2e`; on failure upload `e2e-logs/`; `always` → `make e2e-clean` | `ARTIFACTS_PATH` (shell) | — |\n| `lint.yml` | Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `lint`: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | `golangci` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24; `make lint` | — | — |\n| `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK Tests | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | `sdk`: `sdk-python/**` | `python-sdk-tests` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.12 in `sdk-python/`; `pip install pytest`; `pip install -e .`; `python -m pytest tests/ -v` | Default `working-directory: sdk-python` | — |\n| `python-lint.yml` | Python Lint | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `python`: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, workflow self | `python_lint` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Python 3.10; `pip install ruff`; `ruff check . --config pyproject.toml` | — | — |\n| `test-coverage.yml` | Test Coverage | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | `coverage`: `**` minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` | `coverage` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: free disk space; Go 1.24; `go test` with coverage; step summary; Codecov upload; artifact `go-coverage` | `CODECOV_TOKEN` passed to Codecov action when present | `secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional; declared for `workflow_call`) |\n| `codegen-check.yml` | Codegen Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `codegen`: `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` | `codegen-check` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: Go 1.24.4; `make gen-check` | — | — |\n| `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright Check | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | `copyright`: all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` | `build` | Checkout; paths-filter; if changed: `apt install moreutils`; `make gen-copyright`; `git diff --exit-code` | — | — |\n| `codespell.yml` | Codespell | `pull_request` → `main`, `release-*` | *(none — scans tree after temporarily removing some manifests)* | `codespell` | Backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package.json`, `package-lock.json`; `pip install codespell`; `codespell` with `--check-filenames`, `--skip`, `--ignore-words-list`; restore files | — | — |\n| `build-push-release.yml` | Build and Push Release Images | `push` → `main`; `push` tags `v*.*.*`, `v*.*.*-*` | *(none)* | `build-and-push` | Checkout; Go 1.24.4; Buildx; `docker/login-action` to `ghcr.io`; set `TAG` from ref; `make docker-buildx-push` (workload manager), `docker-buildx-push-router`, `docker-buildx-push-picod` with `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `TAG`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}` | `GITHUB_TOKEN` (registry login) |\n| `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify Plugin Publish | `push` tags `dify-plugin/v*` | *(none)* | `publish` | Download `dify-plugin` CLI 0.0.6; install `yq`; read `manifest.yaml`; package plugin; checkout `author/dify-plugins` with token; move `.difypkg`; branch, commit, push; `gh pr create` to `langgenius/dify-plugins` | `GH_TOKEN` on PR step | `PLUGIN_ACTION` (repo checkout + `gh`; cross-repo PR) |\n| `workflows-approve.yml` | Approve Workflows | `pull_request_target` types `labeled`, `synchronize` → `main`, `release-**` | *(logic: first-time contributor vs `ok-to-test` label)* | `approve` | `github-script`: list contributor PRs; if not first-time or has `ok-to-test`, list `action_required` workflow runs for SHA and approve | — | `GITHUB_TOKEN` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/design.md","time":{"start":1775883627619,"end":1775883627642}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883627650,"sessionID":"ses_28516c8a4ffeyklEf33zHwrJZe","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae99ccd001MlrK2ZW7afeBwY","messageID":"msg_d7ae98495001kBplJQHh1YBsc3","sessionID":"ses_28516c8a4ffeyklEf33zHwrJZe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_556fc4e0aa0d43439378366b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/AR-034-github-actions/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/AR-034-github-actions/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** .github  \n4: **Language:** YAML  \n5: **Size:** L  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Repository Structure & Shared Configuration\n11: \n12: - [ ] **T1.1** Create `.github/workflows/` directory structure\n13:   - Directory: `.github/workflows/`\n14:   - Verify: Directory exists for workflow files\n15: \n16: - [ ] **T1.2** Define reusable path filter configurations\n17:   - Create path filter definitions for: `lint`, `coverage`, `python`, `codegen`, `copyright`\n18:   - Use `dorny/paths-filter` action patterns\n19:   - Verify: All path filters documented in workflow comments\n20: \n21: - [ ] **T1.3** Set up environment variable conventions\n22:   - Document standard env vars: `DOCKER_REGISTRY`, `IMAGE_REGISTRY`, `TAG`, `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA`\n23:   - Verify: Consistent naming across all workflows\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## Phase 2: Agentcube CI Workflow (main.yml)\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T2.1** Create `main.yml` workflow file\n30:   - File: `.github/workflows/main.yml`\n31:   - Name: `Agentcube CI Workflow`\n32:   - Verify: Workflow file created with correct name\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T2.2** Define pull_request triggers for main.yml\n35:   - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n36:   - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n37: \n38: - [ ] **T2.3** Create `build` job in main.yml\n39:   - Job ID: `build`\n40:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n41:   - Verify: Job defined with correct runner\n42: \n43: - [ ] **T2.4** Add checkout and Docker setup steps\n44:   - Step: `actions/checkout@v4`\n45:   - Step: `docker/setup-buildx-action@v3`\n46:   - Verify: Repository checkout and Buildx setup complete\n47: \n48: - [ ] **T2.5** Add Docker version verification step\n49:   - Run: `docker --version` and `docker buildx version`\n50:   - Verify: Docker and buildx versions logged\n51: \n52: - [ ] **T2.6** Add make docker-build execution step\n53:   - Run: `make docker-build`\n54:   - Verify: Workload Manager image builds successfully\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Phase 3: E2E Tests Workflow (e2e.yml)\n59: \n60: - [ ] **T3.1** Create `e2e.yml` workflow file\n61:   - File: `.github/workflows/e2e.yml`\n62:   - Name: `Agentcube E2E Tests`\n63:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n64: \n65: - [ ] **T3.2** Define pull_request triggers for e2e.yml\n66:   - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n67:   - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n68: \n69: - [ ] **T3.3** Create `e2e-test` job in e2e.yml\n70:   - Job ID: `e2e-test`\n71:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n72:   - Verify: Job defined\n73: \n74: - [ ] **T3.4** Add Go 1.23 setup step\n75:   - Use: `actions/setup-go@v5` with `go-version: '1.23'`\n76:   - Verify: Go 1.23 installed\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T3.5** Add Kind cluster installation step\n79:   - Use: `helm/kind-action@v1` with `install_only: true`, `version: v0.30.0`, `cluster_name: agentcube-e2e`\n80:   - Verify: Kind v0.30.0 installed without cluster creation\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T3.6** Set ARTIFACTS_PATH environment variable\n83:   - Env: `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n84:   - Verify: Environment variable set for log collection\n85: \n86: - [ ] **T3.7** Add make e2e execution step\n87:   - Run: `make e2e`\n88:   - Verify: E2E tests execute via run_e2e.sh\n89: \n90: - [ ] **T3.8** Add failure log upload step\n91:   - Use: `actions/upload-artifact@v4` with `e2e-logs/` on failure\n92:   - Condition: `if: failure()`\n93:   - Verify: Logs uploaded on test failure\n94: \n95: - [ ] **T3.9** Add cleanup step with always condition\n96:   - Run: `make e2e-clean`\n97:   - Condition: `if: always()`\n98:   - Verify: Kind cluster cleaned up after tests\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Phase 4: Lint Workflow (lint.yml)\n103: \n104: - [ ] **T4.1** Create `lint.yml` workflow file\n105:   - File: `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n106:   - Name: `Lint`\n107:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n108: \n109: - [ ] **T4.2** Define pull_request triggers for lint.yml\n110:   - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n111:   - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n112: \n113: - [ ] **T4.3** Create `golangci` job in lint.yml\n114:   - Job ID: `golangci`\n115:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n116:   - Verify: Job defined\n117: \n118: - [ ] **T4.4** Add paths-filter for Go code changes\n119:   - Filter ID: `lint`\n120:   - Paths: `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n121:   - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n122:   - Verify: Path filter detects Go-related changes\n123: \n124: - [ ] **T4.5** Add conditional Go 1.24 setup\n125:   - Use: `actions/setup-go@v5` with `go-version: '1.24'`\n126:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.lint == 'true'`\n127:   - Verify: Go setup only when Go code changes\n128: \n129: - [ ] **T4.6** Add make lint execution step\n130:   - Run: `make lint`\n131:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.lint == 'true'`\n132:   - Verify: golangci-lint runs on changed code\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## Phase 5: Python SDK Tests Workflow (python-sdk-tests.yml)\n137: \n138: - [ ] **T5.1** Create `python-sdk-tests.yml` workflow file\n139:   - File: `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml`\n140:   - Name: `Python SDK Tests`\n141:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n142: \n143: - [ ] **T5.2** Define triggers for python-sdk-tests.yml\n144:   - Trigger: `pull_request`, `merge_group`\n145:   - Verify: Both trigger types configured\n146: \n147: - [ ] **T5.3** Create `python-sdk-tests` job\n148:   - Job ID: `python-sdk-tests`\n149:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n150:   - Working directory: `sdk-python`\n151:   - Verify: Job defined with correct working directory\n152: \n153: - [ ] **T5.4** Add paths-filter for SDK changes\n154:   - Filter ID: `sdk`\n155:   - Paths: `sdk-python/**`\n156:   - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n157:   - Verify: Path filter detects SDK changes\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T5.5** Add Python 3.12 setup step\n160:   - Use: `actions/setup-python@v5` with `python-version: '3.12'`\n161:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'`\n162:   - Verify: Python 3.12 installed in sdk-python directory\n163: \n164: - [ ] **T5.6** Add pytest installation step\n165:   - Run: `pip install pytest`\n166:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'`\n167:   - Verify: pytest installed\n168: \n169: - [ ] **T5.7** Add editable package installation step\n170:   - Run: `pip install -e .`\n171:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'`\n172:   - Verify: SDK installed in editable mode\n173: \n174: - [ ] **T5.8** Add pytest execution step\n175:   - Run: `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n176:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.sdk == 'true'`\n177:   - Verify: All SDK tests execute\n178: \n179: ---\n180: \n181: ## Phase 6: Python Lint Workflow (python-lint.yml)\n182: \n183: - [ ] **T6.1** Create `python-lint.yml` workflow file\n184:   - File: `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`\n185:   - Name: `Python Lint`\n186:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n187: \n188: - [ ] **T6.2** Define pull_request triggers for python-lint.yml\n189:   - Trigger: `pull_request` to `main` and `release-*` branches\n190:   - Verify: Correct branch targets configured\n191: \n192: - [ ] **T6.3** Create `python_lint` job in python-lint.yml\n193:   - Job ID: `python_lint`\n194:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n195:   - Verify: Job defined\n196: \n197: - [ ] **T6.4** Add paths-filter for Python code changes\n198:   - Filter ID: `python`\n199:   - Paths: `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`\n200:   - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n201:   - Verify: Path filter detects Python-related changes\n202: \n203: - [ ] **T6.5** Add Python 3.10 setup step\n204:   - Use: `actions/setup-python@v5` with `python-version: '3.10'`\n205:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'`\n206:   - Verify: Python 3.10 installed\n207: \n208: - [ ] **T6.6** Add Ruff installation step\n209:   - Run: `pip install ruff`\n210:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'`\n211:   - Verify: Ruff installed\n212: \n213: - [ ] **T6.7** Add Ruff check execution step\n214:   - Run: `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n215:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.python == 'true'`\n216:   - Working directory: repository root\n217:   - Verify: Ruff linting runs from repo root\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Phase 7: Test Coverage Workflow (test-coverage.yml)\n222: \n223: - [ ] **T7.1** Create `test-coverage.yml` workflow file\n224:   - File: `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml`\n225:   - Name: `Test Coverage`\n226:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T7.2** Define triggers for test-coverage.yml\n229:   - Trigger: `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call`\n230:   - Verify: All three trigger types configured\n231: \n232: - [ ] **T7.3** Add workflow_call inputs for CODECOV_TOKEN\n233:   - Input: `CODECOV_TOKEN` (optional, string)\n234:   - Verify: Token can be passed from reusable workflows\n235: \n236: - [ ] **T7.4** Create `coverage` job in test-coverage.yml\n237:   - Job ID: `coverage`\n238:   - Runner: `ubuntu-latest`\n239:   - Verify: Job defined\n240: \n241: - [ ] **T7.5** Add paths-filter for coverage\n242:   - Filter ID: `coverage`\n243:   - Paths: `**` excluding `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`\n244:   - Use: `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n245:   - Verify: Path filter excludes non-code files\n246: \n247: - [ ] **T7.6** Add free disk space step\n248:   - Run: Disk cleanup commands for runner\n249:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'`\n250:   - Verify: More disk space available for Go modules\n251: \n252: - [ ] **T7.7** Add Go 1.24 setup step\n253:   - Use: `actions/setup-go@v5` with `go-version: '1.24'`\n254:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'`\n255:   - Verify: Go 1.24 installed\n256: \n257: - [ ] **T7.8** Add go test with coverage step\n258:   - Run: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n259:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true'`\n260:   - Verify: Coverage report generated\n261: \n262: - [ ] **T7.9** Add coverage summary to GitHub step summary\n263:   - Run: Generate coverage percentage and write to `$GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY`\n264:   - Verify: Coverage displayed in workflow UI\n265: \n266: - [ ] **T7.10** Add Codecov upload step\n267:   - Use: `codecov/codecov-action@v4`\n268:   - With: `token: ${{ secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN }}`, `files: coverage.out`\n269:   - Condition: `if: steps.filter.outputs.coverage == 'true' && secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN != ''`\n270:   - Verify: Coverage uploaded to Codecov when token available\n271: \n272: - [ ] **T7.11** Add coverage artifact upload step\n273:   - Use: `actions/upload-artifact@v4` with name `go-coverage`, path `coverage.out`\n274:   - Verify: Coverage file available as artifact\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ## Phase 8: Codegen Check Workflow (codegen-check.yml)\n279: \n280: - [ ] **T8.1** Create `codegen-check.yml` workflow file\n281:   - File: `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml`\n282:   - Name: `Codegen Check`\n283:   - Verify: Workflow file created\n284: \n285: - [ ] **T8.2** Define pull_request triggers