{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884060934,"sessionID":"ses_28516c8a4ffeyklEf33zHwrJZe","part":{"id":"prt_d7af01a02001sB2b9hwBEqBfmi","messageID":"msg_d7af00e0a00157gdkwHr9aRqAv","sessionID":"ses_28516c8a4ffeyklEf33zHwrJZe","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_69c9a4abe5cc4384bc5a1692","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AgentCube E2E Tests\n\nThis directory contains end-to-end tests for the AgentCube platform.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Go 1.23+\n- Python 3.10+\n- Kind v0.30.0+\n- Helm 3.x\n- Docker\n\n## Running E2E Tests\n\n### Full E2E Test Suite\n\n```bash\nmake e2e\n```\n\nThis will:\n1. Create a Kind cluster named `agentcube-e2e`\n2. Install agent-sandbox CRDs and controllers\n3. Build and load local Docker images\n4. Install AgentCube via Helm\n5. Apply E2E fixtures (echo agent, code interpreter)\n6. Run Go and Python E2E tests\n7. Clean up the cluster\n\n### Manual Test Execution\n\n```bash\n# Set up environment\nexport WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=http://localhost:8080\nexport ROUTER_URL=http://localhost:8081\nexport API_TOKEN=$(kubectl -n agentcube create token e2e-test --duration=24h)\n\n# Run Go tests\ngo test -v ./test/e2e/...\n\n# Run Python tests\npython test/e2e/test_codeinterpreter.py\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\nEnvironment variables:\n- `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME`: Kind cluster name (default: `agentcube-e2e`)\n- `E2E_CLEAN_CLUSTER`: Delete existing cluster before tests (default: `true`)\n- `E2E_SKIP_SETUP`: Skip cluster setup (default: `false`)\n- `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE`: Kubernetes namespace (default: `agentcube`)\n- `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION`: Agent sandbox version (default: `v0.1.1`)\n- `ARTIFACTS_PATH`: Path for log artifacts on failure\n\n## Fixtures\n\n- `echo_agent.yaml`: Simple echo agent for testing router invocation\n- `e2e_code_interpreter.yaml`: CodeInterpreter resource for testing\n- `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`: CodeInterpreter with warm pool enabled\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Collect Logs Manually\n\n```bash\n./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh 2>&1 | tee e2e.log\n```\n\n### Clean Up\n\n```bash\nmake e2e-clean\n```\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/test/e2e/README.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.github/workflows/main.yml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.github/workflows/e2e.yml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.github/workflows/lint.yml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.github/workflows/python-lint.yml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.github/workflows/codespell.yml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bail